description:
§7 G0 + RCON-01 + §6 artifacts 1–2. This is a gate container; its process prerequisites are P0.1–P0.3 only. P0.4/C-10 does not block durability.

Exit:
- protocol, manifest, registers, and required review inputs are tracked;
- fresh-clone restore proves the declared source baseline and control-plane snapshot are recoverable without local memory;
- one writer owns each mutable artifact and concurrent inputs are frozen;
- tracker state is non-normative and points to validated tracked records.

G0.4 is the fan-in restore drill and depends on G0.1–G0.3. (§4 RCON-01; §6; §7 G0)

The §8 owner-decision queue, dependency-ordered; none is answered by the reconciliation.

P0 is split into four atomic decisions so C-10 does not block durability. P1–P5 now exist as tier containers. Stable contradiction-specific decision leaves are instantiated; remaining product-cell decisions are cut under the G0.3 record schema.

Rules:
- every accepted outcome is an immutable tracked owner record with approval evidence;
- tracker status/comments are non-normative pointers;
- cross-tier contradictions depend on every relevant decision rather than an exclusive tier bucket;
- G2 consumes contradiction decisions; G3 consumes remaining contract-cell decisions; G4 implements verification.

C-10 routes through P0 release authority. C-07 spans P1/P2, C-11 spans P2/P4, and C-12 spans P2/P5. (§5–§8; RCON-01–RCON-10)

§7 G0 restore acceptance; depends on G0.1–G0.3.

From a fresh clone with no local _scratch memory:
- obtain the tracked control-plane snapshot;
- follow the manifest to reconstruct source baseline 89be90bc…;
- recover protocol, S1–S9, predecessor, and register state;
- verify hashes, schema versions, tracker snapshot, references, and single-writer declarations.

This is the objective G0 fan-in signal and must not run before all three inputs are complete. (§4 RCON-01; §6 artifact 1; §7 G0)
